---
description: Show current ITL 1C development status
agent: code
---

Run the helper directly from the current project directory:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\.agents\skills\1c-workflow\scripts\agent-1c.ps1 -Action status
```

On success, return a structured Markdown report with no prose paragraphs. Use the headings `Git`, `Development context`, `Verification`, `MCP`, and `Worktrees` only when the helper prints matching data, with one `- Label: value` field per line. Include the current Git branch and worktree state; current/main worktree paths, branch type, extension, and infobase; verification freshness and result paths; MCP freshness/status; and every printed active worktree name and path. Use only helper values, preserve its `<none>`, `<never>`, and `<not set>` markers, and omit unavailable sections. If the helper fails, report the actual error. Do not switch folders automatically.
